# FarmTech Environment Variables Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES - These must be set for the application to function
# =============================================================================

# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard at https://supabase.com/dashboard
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Cloudinary Configuration  
# Get these from your Cloudinary dashboard at https://cloudinary.com/console
VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_cloud_name
VITE_CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_cloudinary_api_key
VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=your_upload_preset_name

# Application Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME=FarmTech
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL VARIABLES - These enhance functionality but are not required
# =============================================================================

# Admin Configuration (Optional - for admin access)
VITE_ADMIN_SECRET_CODE=your_admin_secret_code
VITE_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@yourdomain.com

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# =============================================================================

# For Netlify Deployment:
# 1. Set these variables in your Netlify dashboard under Site Settings > Environment Variables
# 2. Only variables prefixed with VITE_ will be available in the client-side code
# 3. Never commit sensitive keys to version control
# 4. The VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is safe to expose as it's designed for client-side use
# 5. Keep VITE_CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET out of client-side code (not included here)

# For Local Development:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Fill in your actual values
# 3. The .env file is gitignored and won't be committed

# Security Notes:
# - VITE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY should NEVER be used in client-side code
# - Use Row Level Security (RLS) in Supabase for data protection
# - Cloudinary upload presets should be configured with appropriate restrictions
# - Admin credentials should use strong passwords and be rotated regularly

# Required for Build Process:
# - VITE_SUPABASE_URL: Required for Supabase client initialization
# - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: Required for Supabase authentication
# - VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME: Required for image uploads
# - VITE_CLOUDINARY_API_KEY: Required for Cloudinary integration
# - VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET: Required for secure uploads

# Platform-Specific Notes:
# - Web builds use CAPACITOR_PLATFORM=web (set automatically in build script)
# - Native builds use full Capacitor plugins
# - Environment validation runs at application startup